description.narrative: COs and partners are supported by ROSA through cross-cutting policy analysis and technical advice to build capacity to anticipate and respond to social and economic changes, and promote an enabling policy environment for equity and children's rights., which contributes to Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid), Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Comprehensive, sustainable and enabling environment that leaves no child behind is supported by policies, programmes, strategies, budgets and actions of Governments, regional institutions, private sector, media, financial institutions, UN and UNICEF country programmes in South Asia, in development and humanitarian contexts.

description.narrative: In 2019 about 170 million children were living under the national poverty line in South Asia and current economic growth projections suggest that the incidence of monetary poverty will be similar among children in 2022 because it will take about three years or more for the economies to recover to pre-COVID-19 levels. Countries in the region responded swiftly expanding their social protection programmes, reaching unprecedented levels. As the stimulus packages wane, safeguarding social spending and the gains in coverage of social protection will remain a key priority for achieving progress towards the headline results.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:27/12/2021
